  }
}

(function(){
  const year = document.getElementById('year');
  if (year) year.textContent = String(new Date().getFullYear());
})();


Footer content constraints (what to tell Claude Code)

Keep links stable across the site for crawl consistency

Do not hide links behind accordions on desktop

Newsletter form should degrade gracefully (works even without JS)

Use real a href links with descriptive anchor text

Keep the disclaimer visible and short

Optional enhancement (recommended)

If you want a slightly more premium feel:

Add a tiny “Back to top” link on the bottom right

Add a “Sources” link in the legal section that leads to a page explaining how you reference Centris, APCIQ, Bank of Canada, etc.
